<blockquote class="uncited"><div><br />I also recieved an error for not including a character encoding. I don't know if that is what triggered the error. I haven't desided on an encoding yet.<br /></div></blockquote><br /><br />You should have received an error for the <dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>http-equiv</code></dd></dl> not being the Character Set. Presently, Character Set is the only <dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>http-equiv</code></dd></dl> allowed in the specification.<br /><br />If that was the only error, I would be very pleased.<br /><br />As has been written before, HTTP header elements should be the preferred method over Meta Data.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=6">sfraser</a> — Mon Apr 30, 2007 12:38 am</p><hr />
