<title type="html"><![CDATA[A need to expand meta http-equiv attributes.]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=39&amp;p=175#p175"><![CDATA[
Just to be clear, I started <a href="http://www.webcaptions.org" class="postlink">webcaptions.org</a>. I am creating pages that contain copywrite sensitive information. These pages are in hidden directories for the source author to review before I get permission to make them availible to the public.<br /><br />I'm afraid that someone determined will stumble onto a hidden folder and find information before I recieve permission to make it public. That's why I want to include a temporary expire meta tag. Then when the page expires, I can remove or update the page. Then, unless a hacker has saved the page it will be updated or removed without a browser cache backup.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=59">wgabrie</a> — Thu Apr 26, 2007 7:26 pm</p><hr />
