<entry>
<author><name><![CDATA[wgabrie]]></name></author>
<updated>2007-04-24T01:07:47+00:00</updated>
<id>https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=39&amp;p=157#p157</id>
<link href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=39&amp;p=157#p157"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[A need to expand meta http-equiv attributes.]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=39&amp;p=157#p157"><![CDATA[
I want to use meta tags to make a page expire on the date I choose. Supporting User Agents will refresh their cache after that date.<br /><br />The HTTP-EQUIV is/was used to process a webpage with these values: content-type, expires, refresh, set-cookie. I don't know the state of Metadata and UAs, but, I think UA support is stalled to whatever point it's at now.<br /><br />I'm not saying UAs should support Metadata they don't understand. I do think they should keep the meta knowledge they know now.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=59">wgabrie</a> — Tue Apr 24, 2007 1:07 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
